## Larger Companies

A for-profit organization that exceeds either eligibility threshold is not
licensed under these terms. Use by such an organization requires a separate
commercial license from the copyright holder.

## Definitions

"Affiliate" means any entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under
common control with an organization. "Control" means the direct or indirect
power to direct an entity's management or policies, whether through ownership,
contract, or otherwise.

"Gross Revenue" means all revenue recognized before expenses, deductions, and
taxes.

"Funding Raised" means the aggregate gross proceeds received since formation
from external financing, including equity, debt, convertible instruments,
SAFEs, grants, and similar financing.

